22:04.288 --> 22:05.738
Isn't that right, Jordan?

22:05.772 --> 22:07.878
I guess I just find it
a little disturbing

22:07.912 --> 22:14.367
that society says girls wear skirts and dresses
and boys wear pants and cargo shorts.

22:14.402 --> 22:16.749
It's all the same fabric
cut differently.

22:16.783 --> 22:18.820
We're all the same people,
raised differently.

22:18.854 --> 22:21.650
So, wearing a skirt is just your way to rebel against society.

22:21.685 --> 22:22.686
I understand that.

22:22.720 --> 22:23.756
It's not rebelling,

22:23.790 --> 22:25.965
it's just simply acknowledging
the fact that

22:25.999 --> 22:28.139
this stereotype is bullshit.

22:28.174 --> 22:30.279
Why not just wear
what you want to wear?

22:30.314 --> 22:31.626
Be who you want to be?

22:31.660 --> 22:32.834
Yeah, I agree.

22:32.868 --> 22:37.839
You know, makeup was common
with men in the old days.

22:37.873 --> 22:39.081
See?

22:39.116 --> 22:42.257
It's about self liberation.

22:42.291 --> 22:44.570
Free yourself from the
shackles of conformity.

22:44.604 --> 22:46.606
Yeah, sure.

22:46.641 --> 22:48.297
Become unemployed

22:48.332 --> 22:50.230
Get a gun, do drugs

22:50.265 --> 22:52.612
As long as it expresses
your individuality.

22:52.647 --> 22:54.338
Whoa, who said anything
about a gun?

22:54.373 --> 22:57.410
Guns are for pussies
who can't fight.

22:57.445 --> 23:00.206
How about we change the subject?

23:00.240 --> 23:03.416
How do you plan on
supporting a family?

23:03.451 --> 23:05.798
How are you ever going
to finance a house?

23:05.832 --> 23:07.903
I don't need a house.

23:09.042 --> 23:10.803
Jordan, have you
ever been arrested?

23:10.837 --> 23:12.252
- Dad!
- Please!

23:12.287 --> 23:14.323
That's extremely rude.

23:14.358 --> 23:16.015
Jordan, let's eat
the rest upstairs.

23:16.049 --> 23:19.432
I just want to know why he has no regard for the rules put in place.

23:19.467 --> 23:20.709
No, dammit.
Don't...

23:20.744 --> 23:23.678
Jordan, take anything
that he says personally.

23:23.712 --> 23:26.888
He's just, he's a...
he's an old fart.

23:28.027 --> 23:29.546
He just, you know

23:29.580 --> 23:32.756
doesn't want his daughter dating a domestic terrorist, bro.

23:34.585 --> 23:37.726
Domestic terrorists are usually
well educated, white,

23:37.761 --> 23:42.731
ultra religious,
second amendment loving right wing fanatics!

23:42.766 --> 23:47.080
I'm a poor,
unemployed Atheist mutt.

23:47.115 --> 23:49.807
I'm like a father's
dream come true!

23:49.842 --> 23:53.397
You're worse than he is.
I'm eating alone.

23:55.054 --> 23:57.953
It was lovely meeting you all.

23:58.989 --> 24:00.749
Morgan!

24:01.992 --> 24:04.201
- Oh, come on!
- What the hell?

24:04.235 --> 24:05.720
You were a hippie once too.

24:05.754 --> 24:07.894
That's not a hippie!
I was nothing like that!

24:07.929 --> 24:10.276
Morgan is a gay lesbian.

24:10.310 --> 24:12.312
Oh sweetie, your sister
is not a lesbian.

24:12.347 --> 24:14.418
Lesbians like girls, but

24:14.453 --> 24:17.490
if the lesbian is gay,
she likes boys.

24:17.525 --> 24:19.354
She's a gay lesbian.

24:19.388 --> 24:23.220
I'm so confused,
does that mean that he is a straight homosexual?

24:37.165 --> 24:39.339
Wait! Wait!

24:39.374 --> 24:41.721
What?
I'm not a domestic terrorist!

24:43.378 --> 24:45.656
I like where this is going,

24:45.691 --> 24:47.624
just not here.

24:49.142 --> 24:51.213
Good idea, your Dad scares me.

24:51.248 --> 24:54.493
That just cause you scare him.

24:54.527 --> 24:58.669
My place. I have the best view
of the entire city.

24:58.704 --> 25:00.464
Let's go.

25:09.438 --> 25:11.889
- Who are they?
- They're nobody.

25:12.683 --> 25:17.654
Look who's back... with company.

25:17.688 --> 25:20.104
Morgan, this is Misty.
Misty, Morgan.

25:20.139 --> 25:22.072
It's nice to meet you, Misty.

25:22.106 --> 25:23.729
Where did you find her? Church?

25:23.763 --> 25:24.626
Why church?

25:24.661 --> 25:26.490
I'm so sorry, how rude of me.

25:26.525 --> 25:28.768
I'm not used to him bringing
girls home. You know?

25:28.803 --> 25:33.635
They're usually anorexic twinks.
Nice to meet you, Morgan.

25:33.670 --> 25:35.361
Let's go.

25:35.395 --> 25:37.087
Hey, Morgan!

25:37.121 --> 25:39.572
Has he taken your wallet yet?

25:39.607 --> 25:44.439
Yeah, that's what
swept me off my feet.

25:44.473 --> 25:47.718
I want my money tonight
or you're out!

25:56.140 --> 25:57.866
: You live up here?

26:00.282 --> 26:01.767
Told you...

26:02.595 --> 26:04.701
Best view of the city.

26:07.945 --> 26:09.602
You impressed, yet?

26:11.052 --> 26:12.225
Where do you pee?

26:12.260 --> 26:14.952
I have four options.

26:16.126 --> 26:18.059
How do you poop?

26:20.544 --> 26:22.891
Why do you owe that girl money?

26:22.926 --> 26:24.962
Here we go again
with the questions.

26:24.997 --> 26:26.136
Sorry, it's a bad habit.

26:26.170 --> 26:29.760
It's the detective in me. Well?

26:29.795 --> 26:33.868
I borrowed some money from her and haven't paid her back yet.
It's no big deal.

26:33.902 --> 26:35.421
How much?

26:35.455 --> 26:36.456
Seriously?

26:36.491 --> 26:38.182
Was it for drugs?

26:38.217 --> 26:41.047
Wow. No, it was not for drugs.

26:42.048 --> 26:45.293
It was for, believe it or not,
art school.

26:45.327 --> 26:47.122
You go to art school?

26:47.157 --> 26:49.055
I did...

26:49.090 --> 26:53.542
for about seven weeks,
but it was a total scam.

26:55.475 --> 26:57.167
You wanna go inside?

26:57.201 --> 26:59.169
Yeah.

26:59.203 --> 27:00.308
You okay?

27:00.342 --> 27:01.481
Yeah.

27:01.516 --> 27:03.656
Great,
I just get dizzy sometimes.

27:03.691 --> 27:05.071
You afraid of heights?

27:05.106 --> 27:08.696
I love heights!
Let's just go in your palace.

27:15.081 --> 27:16.565
Thanks.

27:24.366 --> 27:26.161
Is she your ex-girlfriend?

27:26.196 --> 27:28.543
She is, isn't she?

27:29.717 --> 27:31.857
For the next five minutes,

27:31.891 --> 27:34.135
no more questions.

27:37.310 --> 27:39.554
Just one more?

27:46.078 --> 27:47.631
OK. Ask your question.

27:47.666 --> 27:50.013
Don't you get lonely up here?

27:51.497 --> 27:53.223
Not really.

27:54.500 --> 27:56.157
That's a lie.

27:56.191 --> 28:00.299
Looking down,
avoiding eye contact, tone changes.

28:00.333 --> 28:03.751
All signs of a big fat lie.

28:05.131 --> 28:07.858
I'm not lonely right now.

28:24.772 --> 28:27.326
I looked so different back then.

28:27.360 --> 28:29.052
Way back when you were innocent.

28:30.778 --> 28:32.780
Which brings us to today.

28:32.814 --> 28:35.644
Paging Doctor Colson at the E.R.

28:40.201 --> 28:43.998
Maybe we should explain why we have the doctor tied up in the closet.

28:44.032 --> 28:47.242
We don't want your family
to get the wrong idea.

28:47.277 --> 28:52.247
Good thinking.
Doctor, you should probably watch this too.

28:55.423 --> 28:57.528
Told you, it's stupid.

28:57.563 --> 28:59.738
Shut it. I'm reading.

29:00.808 --> 29:03.362
He was falling in love. Madly.

29:03.396 --> 29:08.539
But he knew, the queen bee would
never allow them to be together.

29:08.574 --> 29:10.541
The dragonfly boy had an idea

29:10.576 --> 29:15.788
an idea so great,
he was sure that the Queen bee would be fooled

29:15.823 --> 29:20.689
and the princess of bees would now be allowed to love him forever.

29:20.724 --> 29:23.865
He flew up to the cupboard,
opened it

29:23.900 --> 29:27.041
and grabbed a jar of honey.

29:28.905 --> 29:32.287
I love it. You made this?

29:33.323 --> 29:34.807
You really like it?

29:34.842 --> 29:38.121
Yes. They're in love.

29:39.881 --> 29:44.161
It's just a story,
not even a very good one.

29:44.196 --> 29:48.441
Love stories are the only stories worth telling.

29:48.476 --> 29:50.236
Why'd you quit art school?

29:51.306 --> 29:54.447
You're only good if
you do it their way.

29:54.482 --> 29:56.449
If you play by their rules.

29:56.484 --> 29:58.072
My rebel!

29:58.935 --> 30:01.592
Are you the
little dragonfly boy?

30:01.627 --> 30:04.423
No, you are.

30:04.457 --> 30:06.390
I'm the princess bee.

30:12.776 --> 30:14.847
I have to go.

30:16.504 --> 30:18.506
Thought you were
staying the night.

30:18.540 --> 30:21.578
You lost the bet, remember?

30:21.612 --> 30:23.752
Good night, princess.

30:39.907 --> 30:41.391
Baby?

30:44.843 --> 30:50.400
You can't runaway from this.
We need to talk about it.

30:50.434 --> 30:53.127
It's not easy for any of us.

30:54.231 --> 30:56.682
We just...

30:56.716 --> 30:58.857
We just want to do
what's best for you.

30:58.891 --> 31:01.998
Then just act normal
to me again?

31:03.965 --> 31:05.380
Okay.

31:08.280 --> 31:09.557
They're um,

31:09.591 --> 31:11.697
They're sending us to
a specialist.

31:14.424 --> 31:16.702
Your results came in.

31:18.117 --> 31:19.705
It's...

31:21.603 --> 31:22.811
Your situation is--

31:22.846 --> 31:24.296
What did they say?

31:24.330 --> 31:30.095
They're going to take you
right away. In Houston.

31:30.129 --> 31:34.375
If they can fix me there,
they can fix me here.

31:48.596 --> 31:52.048
They can't fix you here, baby.

31:54.740 --> 31:56.293
I'm sorry.

31:57.639 --> 31:59.883
But they can't.

32:04.577 --> 32:06.165
What's going on?

32:07.580 --> 32:08.719
Are you okay, Dad?

32:08.754 --> 32:11.791
Yeah, Buddy. It's okay.

32:16.589 --> 32:18.350
It's okay.

32:25.150 --> 32:26.772
Jordan?

32:32.467 --> 32:34.607
Detective Colossus.

32:34.642 --> 32:36.471
Inspector Clouseau!

32:37.748 --> 32:40.820
Dragonfly boy missed
his princess bee already?

32:40.855 --> 32:44.341
Wait.
I need to tell you something.

32:44.376 --> 32:45.618
You have a boyfriend?

32:45.653 --> 32:48.104
I don't care.
I wasn't born with a jealous bone.

32:48.138 --> 32:51.003
Everybody was born with
a jealous bone, but no.

32:51.038 --> 32:54.420
I don't have a boyfriend.
I have something else.

32:54.455 --> 32:57.665
- Just listen to me.
- I'm listening, what is it?

32:57.699 --> 33:00.219
I have a brain tumor!

33:01.496 --> 33:05.017
A brain tumor? Like what,
a tumor in your brain?

33:05.052 --> 33:09.677
Yep. A brain tumor,
a tumor in my brain.

33:09.711 --> 33:10.747
Does it hurt?

33:10.781 --> 33:11.851
Mmhmm.

33:11.886 --> 33:13.267
Is it serious?

33:13.301 --> 33:15.855
Yes. It is serious.

33:16.960 --> 33:20.308
Well can't a doctor
like suck it out

33:20.343 --> 33:22.034
or do whatever it is
that doctors do?

33:22.069 --> 33:25.382
No. It's in my brain.

33:26.694 --> 33:27.729
But, how?

33:27.764 --> 33:31.664
They found a lump here
two years ago.

33:31.699 --> 33:35.358
They got out all the
malignant cells

33:35.392 --> 33:39.672
but last year, we learned that
it spread to my brain.

33:39.707 --> 33:42.813
It's... irreversible.

33:42.848 --> 33:45.057
Nothing's irreversible.

33:45.092 --> 33:50.890
I came to tell you that's why
I gave you the wrong number.

33:50.925 --> 33:52.099
I still found you.

33:52.133 --> 33:54.791
And that I'm leaving tomorrow.

33:54.825 --> 33:56.103
Where are you going?

33:56.137 --> 34:00.693
Texas. They have to take over
my situation.

34:00.728 --> 34:02.592
When are you coming back?

34:02.626 --> 34:04.939
I don't know.

34:04.973 --> 34:06.285
You don't look sick.

34:06.320 --> 34:10.841
Yeah.
It's what's on the inside that counts.

34:10.876 --> 34:11.532
Wait!

34:13.016 --> 34:17.054
It can't be like this,
just like that. Doesn't feel right.

34:17.089 --> 34:19.609
I know it doesn't.

34:19.643 --> 34:22.335
Wait! Just hear me out!
OK?

34:22.370 --> 34:26.926
If it is irreversible,
they can't do anything right? I can do that.

34:26.960 --> 34:27.996
So why go?

34:28.031 --> 34:31.379
For my family.
They need this.

34:31.414 --> 34:32.346
Wait!

34:32.380 --> 34:35.487
Just, what?
Just, just stop saying wait!

34:35.521 --> 34:37.454
I meant stay.

34:37.489 --> 34:38.489
Fuck.

34:49.984 --> 34:51.606
See that?

34:51.641 --> 34:54.505
You probably thought it was a couple of lunatics that kidnapped you.

34:54.540 --> 34:57.129
In reality, we're just
two birds in love.

34:57.164 --> 34:59.062
Hey, you okay in there?

34:59.097 --> 35:03.342
Uh, just...
Uh, just my...

35:03.377 --> 35:04.585
Morgan? Morgan!

35:12.731 --> 35:15.975
♪ ...You're my best friend

35:17.460 --> 35:23.431
♪ M-O-R-G-A-N

35:24.536 --> 35:27.297
♪ When you went

35:28.712 --> 35:32.026
♪ I crossed my heart

35:32.060 --> 35:35.098
♪ Promised you

35:35.133 --> 35:38.274
♪ To never be apart

35:39.723 --> 35:46.005
♪ Cause you're my little girl
you're my best friend. ♪

35:47.593 --> 35:53.634
♪ M-O-R-G-A-N

35:59.571 --> 36:03.195
The tumor in Morgan's brain
is spreading very quickly.

36:03.230 --> 36:06.647
We ran numerous tests and right now we only have one option.

36:06.681 --> 36:10.892
Do it again with a wave of radiation and see if it reactions.

36:10.927 --> 36:14.102
We came here because you
guys are the best.

36:15.207 --> 36:17.382
Tell me you can do
something to help her.

36:17.416 --> 36:20.074
The chances of her recovery
are very low.

36:20.108 --> 36:23.111
We'll continue to do
everything we can.

36:23.146 --> 36:25.217
But this condition

36:25.252 --> 36:27.392
it never ends well.

36:27.426 --> 36:33.191
What we can do is make her transition as comfortable as possible.

36:33.225 --> 36:36.401
Eliminate most of the pain.

36:36.435 --> 36:41.233
But it's not going to be easy
for her or her family.

36:42.579 --> 36:45.410
Y-you're tell me my daughter
is going to die?

36:45.444 --> 36:48.827
When we get to a point where there is nothing more to be done,

36:48.861 --> 36:51.312
we recommend that you take her.

36:51.347 --> 36:53.763
Where she's home
with her family.

36:53.797 --> 36:58.008
We should start radiation here
as soon as possible.

36:58.043 --> 37:01.115
We'll make an incision,
take some blood

37:01.149 --> 37:03.151
some tissues,
some bone samples

37:03.186 --> 37:06.672
to gauge the affectivity
of it now.

37:06.707 --> 37:09.088
May I begin the prep?

37:09.848 --> 37:12.540
What if I take her home today?

37:13.886 --> 37:16.061
What should we expect to see?

37:16.924 --> 37:19.340
More frequent headaches
will emerge.

37:19.375 --> 37:23.620
Confusion, numbness, maybe
some personality changes.

37:23.655 --> 37:28.384
Difficulty in speech
and possibly seizures.

37:28.418 --> 37:30.834
We recommend
you don't leave yet.

37:32.871 --> 37:35.183
Three months.

37:36.288 --> 37:42.398
You know, it doesn't
really matter where that is.

37:42.432 --> 37:47.368
You start your prep and
then we will just...

37:49.405 --> 37:51.890
If it doesn't work,
we'll take her home.

37:51.924 --> 37:53.340
Of course.

37:53.374 --> 37:57.551
Three... Two... One...
He shoots!

37:57.585 --> 37:58.621
He misses!

37:58.655 --> 38:00.450
But there's still a
half-second on the clock,

38:00.485 --> 38:04.005
Bailey with the rebound
Wha-pow-pow-pow!

38:06.629 --> 38:09.183
And the crowd goes wild!

38:15.085 --> 38:16.846
We're all set.

38:20.021 --> 38:22.127
You ready to go, my love?

38:23.577 --> 38:26.580
The dragonfly boy
covered himself in honey.

38:26.614 --> 38:31.964
As he did this,
the dragonflies above began to leave one by one.

38:31.999 --> 38:35.727
The dragonfly boy was
now all alone.

38:35.761 --> 38:39.075
The dragonfly boy walked
all day and all night,

38:39.109 --> 38:41.802
covered head to toe in honey.

38:41.836 --> 38:47.359
Many bees from the local village hives
began to be attracted to his coat of honey.

38:47.394 --> 38:49.879
The bees would swarm
to the dragonfly boy,

38:49.913 --> 38:53.331
sticking to the dragonfly boy's
honey-glued body.

38:53.365 --> 38:56.368
Soon, covering the
dragonfly boy entirely

38:56.403 --> 38:58.957
making him look no longer
like a dragonfly,

38:58.991 --> 39:02.961
but now as a giant bee himself.

39:02.995 --> 39:05.653
He arrived at the Queen Bee's
honeycombed castle

39:05.688 --> 39:09.036
and is approached
by the royal bee guard.

39:09.070 --> 39:10.658
"May I help you?"

39:10.693 --> 39:14.593
"Yes, I am a prince bee
from a far away kingdom"

39:14.628 --> 39:18.010
"I am here to offer my heart
to the Princess Bee."

39:18.045 --> 39:20.427
"We will take you to the Queen"

39:21.704 --> 39:25.052
Hey, stranger.
What are you doing?

39:25.086 --> 39:28.435
Just doodling. Why?

39:29.884 --> 39:32.266
It's like an orgy down there,

39:32.300 --> 39:35.373
everybody's so fucked
out of their brains.

39:35.407 --> 39:37.892
Thought you were into that.

39:39.204 --> 39:41.689
Well it depends who's involved.

39:41.724 --> 39:43.104
You wanna go down there?

39:43.139 --> 39:46.245
- Come on.
- I was just leaving.

39:47.385 --> 39:50.042
Don't be such a grouch.
Have a drink.

39:50.077 --> 39:52.769
- Come on!
- What are you on right now?

39:52.804 --> 39:55.945
Wine! God.

40:02.469 --> 40:03.331
Come on.

40:21.419 --> 40:23.282
How have you been?

40:24.663 --> 40:27.459
You'd know if you
were around, but...

40:27.494 --> 40:29.806
You're always up here.

40:29.841 --> 40:31.739
Coloring or

40:31.774 --> 40:35.398
you know, running around
with that church girl.

40:36.606 --> 40:39.437
I haven't seen her in a while.

40:39.471 --> 40:41.162
Did you rob her blind already?

40:41.197 --> 40:43.026
You don't know
anything about her.

40:43.061 --> 40:45.995
Oh, Jordan. C'mon. Really?

40:47.341 --> 40:50.965
You know she can dress like us,
she can act like us,

40:51.000 --> 40:54.175
but she will never be like us!

40:54.210 --> 40:56.488
I know that type. Yeah?

40:56.523 --> 40:59.353
Her parents bail her out...

40:59.387 --> 41:02.977
Right? Yeah, her life
is so fucking easy.

41:03.012 --> 41:07.706
Like us? There is no "us".
I'm nothing like you!

41:07.741 --> 41:08.914
Whoa!

41:08.949 --> 41:11.365
Leave, Misty!

41:11.399 --> 41:14.437
OK! Chill out, dude!

41:14.472 --> 41:18.061
Did I just, like, insult
your fucking princess?

41:18.096 --> 41:19.477
You know, hey,
have you noticed her?

41:19.511 --> 41:21.168
She has like some, um

41:21.202 --> 41:25.172
speech impediment, you know?
She talks like this.

41:25.206 --> 41:26.622
Yeah, she sounds like
a fucking retard!

41:26.656 --> 41:28.900
Get out! Why can't you
just ever leave?

41:28.934 --> 41:31.868
No, you get out!
You get the fuck out of my roof!

41:31.903 --> 41:33.836
- It's not your fucking roof.
- No! Yeah!

41:33.870 --> 41:37.356
I don't give a shit! OK?

41:44.398 --> 41:47.850
You've always been
a fucking loser.

41:47.884 --> 41:52.855
You quit, quit, quit!
Quit, quit, quit, quit!

41:52.889 --> 41:54.581
That's what you do!

41:54.615 --> 41:57.480
That's the only thing
you know what to do. OK?

41:57.515 --> 42:00.207
And she knows that.
She pities you.

42:00.241 --> 42:03.693
She loves me.
And I love her.

42:08.387 --> 42:10.217
Where's my money?

42:10.251 --> 42:11.736
I'm getting it.

42:44.009 --> 42:45.355
You're out, OK?

42:45.390 --> 42:48.945
I don't give a fuck about your stupid little shit drawings!

42:48.980 --> 42:52.190
All this fucking shit!
I don't give a shit!

42:52.224 --> 42:54.157
Get the fuck out!

42:54.192 --> 42:56.608
I want my money tonight.
If not...

42:56.643 --> 42:59.266
this whole thing's
gonna go out. OK?

42:59.300 --> 43:03.753
You understand?
Fuck you!

43:04.892 --> 43:07.826
They're taking me apart
piece by piece, Mom.

43:07.861 --> 43:10.311
- When I die--
- No, don't say that.

43:10.346 --> 43:12.555
It's irreversible, mom.

43:12.590 --> 43:15.385
When it happens,
it can't be here.

43:15.420 --> 43:17.595
Promise me it won't be here!

43:17.629 --> 43:20.080
They're doing everything that they can.
I promise you that.

43:20.114 --> 43:21.357
Promise her it won't be
here, Mom.

43:21.391 --> 43:22.807
Bailey!

43:22.841 --> 43:26.120
Morgan, I promise you
I won't let anyone keep you here

43:26.155 --> 43:29.227
one second longer than you
want to be, alright?

43:29.261 --> 43:30.815
Should we step outside?

43:30.849 --> 43:33.749
No, this is about me!
I want to hear it!

43:45.208 --> 43:46.865
- They can't.
- Take me home!

43:46.900 --> 43:49.972
I hear they can manage your pain much
better than we can at home, baby.

43:50.006 --> 43:51.594
Take me home! Bailey?

43:51.629 --> 43:52.768
We're going home.

43:52.802 --> 43:55.529
No, Bailey! Just let us
think. OK?

43:56.668 --> 44:02.778
Please, whatever time I
have left. Let me have it.

44:21.417 --> 44:23.039
Why didn't my key work?

44:23.074 --> 44:26.733
Probably because Misty
changed the locks.

44:26.767 --> 44:28.044
Why?

44:29.114 --> 44:30.771
To keep Jordan out.

44:30.806 --> 44:31.703
I'm Jordan.

44:31.738 --> 44:34.568
Not today princess.

44:34.602 --> 44:36.018
What are you talking about?

44:37.571 --> 44:39.538
So I take it that
this is the hive,

44:39.573 --> 44:42.162
and I'm like
one of the guardian bees.

44:42.196 --> 44:44.164
How big is my stinger?

44:44.198 --> 44:48.133
The dragonfly boy was led
into the Queen's palace.

44:48.168 --> 44:52.206
She looked the dragonfly boy
up and down and said

44:52.241 --> 44:54.692
"What hive are you from?"

44:54.726 --> 44:58.523
"I am a prince from a hive
deep in the northern forest,

44:58.557 --> 45:00.663
so deep you probably
never heard of it".

45:00.698 --> 45:05.633
"I am the queen! I heard of
every hive worth hearing about!

45:05.668 --> 45:10.017
Tell me, young prince. Is your
land rich in honey?"

45:10.052 --> 45:12.951
"Yes, My hive is
full of honey."

45:12.986 --> 45:16.506
The queen's eyes light up
with a greedy golden glow.

45:16.541 --> 45:21.063
"Then I will be twice as rich!
Bring out the princess!"

45:21.097 --> 45:25.032
The bee guards open a
honeycombed door.

45:25.067 --> 45:28.795
There stands the beautiful
princess bee.

45:28.829 --> 45:32.074
Her eyes meet the
dragonfly boy's eyes.

45:32.108 --> 45:34.801
"You are the strangest bee
I have ever seen,

45:34.835 --> 45:38.977
but I can see in your eyes,
that you are a kind prince."

45:39.012 --> 45:42.532
The dragonfly boy, more happy
than he has ever been,

45:42.567 --> 45:45.535
embraces his beloved
princess bee.

45:45.570 --> 45:47.227
And even though it was
quite romantic,

45:47.261 --> 45:52.197
the dragonfly boy knew he had just fallen into a very sticky situation.

45:52.232 --> 45:55.925
The princess bee became
stuck to the dragonfly boy

45:55.960 --> 45:59.342
just like all the
other bees before her.

46:00.550 --> 46:03.657
The queen bee was outraged!

47:12.450 --> 47:14.659
What are you doing?

47:32.884 --> 47:34.852
Go back to sleep.

48:57.624 --> 48:58.866
Brings out your eyes.

48:59.729 --> 49:02.008
What the hell
are you doing here?

49:02.042 --> 49:03.975
Morgan, is everything okay?

49:04.010 --> 49:08.186
Yeah, it's just a spider.
I captured it!

49:08.221 --> 49:10.499
Okay, I'll be downstairs
if you need me.

49:10.533 --> 49:12.121
I'm fine, Mom!

49:15.159 --> 49:16.401
I missed you.

49:18.231 --> 49:20.267
We can't do this.

49:20.302 --> 49:21.889
It's not fair.

49:21.924 --> 49:23.305
Life's not fair.

49:23.961 --> 49:25.583
It's not good for you.

49:25.617 --> 49:27.309
And it's not good for me.

49:27.343 --> 49:29.104
I'm not good for anyone.
How does that matter?

49:29.138 --> 49:32.383
I like you.
That's how it matters.

49:33.694 --> 49:36.766
I don't want you
to see me like this.

49:36.801 --> 49:39.459
Are you kidding?
I like this new look.

49:39.493 --> 49:42.807
It's very anarchist. It's sexy.

49:44.464 --> 49:48.192
No. I mean...

49:48.226 --> 49:52.713
I don't want you to
see what happens to me.

49:52.748 --> 49:55.164
I want you to remember me

49:55.199 --> 49:57.339
when I was me.

49:57.373 --> 49:58.996
I'm falling apart.

49:59.789 --> 50:02.620
We're all falling apart, Morgan.

50:02.654 --> 50:04.001
It's the nature of this world.

50:04.035 --> 50:07.625
Please, just go away.

50:07.659 --> 50:09.006
I am going away. I just

50:09.040 --> 50:10.455
came here to see if
you wanted to come with.

50:10.490 --> 50:12.802
You can't just run from
what's coming to me.

50:12.837 --> 50:14.321
You can always run.

50:14.356 --> 50:17.048
It may catch you,
but we can always run.

50:17.083 --> 50:19.947
Make that fucker chase you down,
instead of just rolling over

50:19.982 --> 50:21.328
waiting for it.

50:21.363 --> 50:23.020
You don't get it.

50:25.953 --> 50:28.094
Please, leave.

50:28.784 --> 50:31.304
And don't come back.

50:31.338 --> 50:35.894
We won't recognize
each other if you do.

50:35.929 --> 50:37.931
I'm not leaving you.

50:37.965 --> 50:40.140
I don't want you here!

50:41.590 --> 50:43.316
Do you get that?

50:45.042 --> 50:49.046
I don't want to
know you anymore.

50:51.013 --> 50:52.877
Leave or I'll scream.

51:02.956 --> 51:06.408
- You're not dead yet, Morgan.
- I am dead.

51:06.442 --> 51:10.584
Your story ends with "She dies,
the end." Trust me!

51:10.619 --> 51:13.484
You should use your brain
while you still have it.

51:13.518 --> 51:14.657
I'll be waiting.

51:17.591 --> 51:23.252
♪ Drive baby drive,
until your trouble's gone ♪

51:27.222 --> 51:34.988
♪ Run, baby, run,
until it all goes numb ♪

51:39.475 --> 51:43.376
♪ You are the wind,
the flood and the flame ♪

51:43.410 --> 51:45.447
♪ Nothing here
can get in your way ♪

51:45.481 --> 51:49.865
♪ You've come too far to
