51:58.908 --> 52:01.187
♪ Now you're the only
thing in your way ♪

52:06.192 --> 52:14.061
♪ Fly, baby, fly,
until nothing can get you down... ♪

52:18.065 --> 52:20.171
Told you. Not sexy.

52:20.206 --> 52:22.242
Jordan, tell them what
you were doing this whole time.

52:22.277 --> 52:23.623
I was waiting for you.

52:23.657 --> 52:24.658
Tell them!

52:24.693 --> 52:25.832
Fine.

52:25.866 --> 52:28.869
So I was all dressed up
and had nowhere to go.

52:28.904 --> 52:31.907
So, that's exactly where
I went. Nowhere.

52:31.941 --> 52:33.943
And when you're nowhere
in life

52:33.978 --> 52:36.325
that's where bad shit
happens.

52:36.360 --> 52:40.295
Well, well, well.

52:40.329 --> 52:41.434
Look who's here.

52:41.468 --> 52:42.607
Misty?

52:42.642 --> 52:43.919
This him?

52:49.959 --> 52:51.685
Muscolo!

52:52.824 --> 52:55.620
Introduce yourself.

52:55.655 --> 52:58.002
Shame. He was pretty too.

52:58.036 --> 52:59.314
Misty, what is this?

53:02.351 --> 53:05.216
Hey, hey, hey!
Come here! Come here!

53:05.251 --> 53:06.321
Where's my money?

53:06.355 --> 53:08.115
Jordan, just give them
the money!

53:08.150 --> 53:11.567
- Come out and play!
- No! No! Aah!

53:13.293 --> 53:16.123
- No! No, no!
- Listen to me. Listen.

53:16.158 --> 53:17.918
I think you're confused.

53:17.953 --> 53:22.958
I'm not some pinché puto selling pastelitos on the street, man.

53:22.992 --> 53:26.789
I'm a business man. Yeah.

53:26.824 --> 53:31.415
And you interfered
with my business.

53:32.347 --> 53:35.419
Now, I have to call my friend.

53:37.559 --> 53:38.629
This one here.

53:41.632 --> 53:44.013
Say you don't have the money.
Say it.

53:44.048 --> 53:47.500
Say "I don't have the money".

53:47.534 --> 53:52.746
- Say it. Say it! Say it!
- Wait, wait! I don't!

53:52.781 --> 53:55.542
- I don't have all of it!
- Say it!

53:55.577 --> 53:57.889
I just only have part of
it. I smoked most of it.

53:57.924 --> 53:59.753
Oh you smoked my money!

53:59.788 --> 54:02.894
No, he's not lying!

54:02.929 --> 54:04.724
But just like that, yes?

54:06.691 --> 54:08.383
Hey no, man! C'mon!

54:11.972 --> 54:13.491
Hit him again!

54:18.807 --> 54:22.431
Shaddup! I say when it's enough!
Gucho says when it's enough!

54:22.466 --> 54:23.467
Shaddup!

54:24.088 --> 54:25.883
Listen to me.

54:25.917 --> 54:27.919
Listen to me, pretty face.

54:27.954 --> 54:31.129
I'm gonna give you two days.
OK?

54:31.164 --> 54:36.825
One, two days to give me
my money

54:36.859 --> 54:38.136
All my money.

54:38.171 --> 54:39.862
You can decide to run away.

54:39.897 --> 54:43.728
You can go far to whatever
you want. The Bahamas, surfing!

54:43.763 --> 54:46.006
Whatever the fuck you want!

54:46.041 --> 54:47.456
But I'm gonna find you.

54:47.491 --> 54:50.425
I'm gonna cut your little dickie
right there.

54:51.736 --> 54:56.085
I'm gonna make a burrito.
I'm gonna eat it.

54:56.120 --> 54:58.225
And then, I'm gonna kill you.

54:58.260 --> 54:59.537
You understand?

54:59.572 --> 55:02.229
What the hell is going on here?

55:02.264 --> 55:03.541
None of your business.

55:03.576 --> 55:04.853
This is my business.

55:04.887 --> 55:07.304
Oh, and this is my gun!

55:11.894 --> 55:13.275
Listen man,

55:13.310 --> 55:16.796
We caught this piece of shit
stealing purses from your club.

55:16.830 --> 55:19.074
We were doing your job.

55:19.108 --> 55:22.180
I don't like doing your job.
I got my own job!

55:22.215 --> 55:24.321
That doesn't make me happy!

55:25.149 --> 55:26.461
Not happy about that!

55:26.495 --> 55:29.187
Misty? You have your purse?

55:29.222 --> 55:32.363
Hey! Grab yours? Vamanos!

55:34.676 --> 55:35.780
Vamos!

55:35.815 --> 55:37.472
Adios.

55:43.305 --> 55:44.824
Keep walking.

55:52.383 --> 55:54.351
Don't come back here.

56:27.556 --> 56:30.904
Just wondering when
you'd be coming back for those.

56:33.528 --> 56:35.495
You knew these were
under your bed?

56:35.530 --> 56:38.774
Took me less than five minutes
to find them.

56:53.824 --> 56:57.034
What happened to your face?

56:57.068 --> 56:59.001
Someone broke my heart

56:59.036 --> 57:01.314
and it spread to my face.

57:01.348 --> 57:03.385
I missed you.

57:15.259 --> 57:16.916
I missed you too.

57:17.986 --> 57:19.919
I missed you too.

57:24.993 --> 57:26.891
Follow me.

57:44.564 --> 57:46.877
Wait! What are you doing?

57:46.911 --> 57:48.395
I want to be with you.

57:48.430 --> 57:50.363
I want to live with you.
I want to look like you.

57:50.397 --> 57:51.951
Everything.

57:52.710 --> 57:53.918
You can't, I'm...

57:53.953 --> 57:56.403
I don't care how much
time we have together.

57:56.438 --> 58:00.994
Dragonflies only live for three months and look how happy they are.

58:01.029 --> 58:02.962
How do you know they're happy?

58:03.997 --> 58:06.448
Have you ever heard of
a depressed dragonfly?

58:08.277 --> 58:09.486
No.

58:16.182 --> 58:18.529
Are you sure about this?

58:18.564 --> 58:21.359
This might be a
very stupid idea.

58:21.394 --> 58:22.913
Let's just be stupid.

58:23.914 --> 58:26.088
Make it so that no one
can tell us apart.

58:45.763 --> 58:49.733
♪ Forever me and forever you

58:52.149 --> 58:54.772
♪ The promise we made

58:55.704 --> 58:59.225
♪ We hold as the truth

58:59.259 --> 59:02.987
♪ All we ever hear

59:03.022 --> 59:06.163
♪ All that was said

59:06.197 --> 59:09.580
♪ As dreams eclipse feeling

59:09.615 --> 59:13.480
♪ Death, dying or dead

59:13.515 --> 59:17.657
♪ Forever me and forever you

59:20.557 --> 59:24.664
♪ Forever me and forever you

59:28.737 --> 59:32.430
♪ And Heaven don't make

59:33.328 --> 59:34.398
♪ A High...

59:34.432 --> 59:36.158
Busted!

59:37.746 --> 59:39.127
Bailes! Get out!

59:40.438 --> 59:42.475
Keep it down, Mom and
Dad will hear you!

59:42.509 --> 59:44.339
But they sent me up
to wake you up.

59:44.373 --> 59:46.444
They know he's here?

59:48.170 --> 59:49.758
Who lit your face up?

59:49.793 --> 59:50.621
Your sister did.

59:50.656 --> 59:52.312
She's a wild animal
in the sack.

59:52.347 --> 59:53.555
Shut up!

59:53.590 --> 59:54.970
Tell them all I'll
be right down.

59:55.005 --> 59:57.007
Mom wants to know if
your guest will be

59:57.041 --> 59:58.595
staying for breakfast.

59:58.629 --> 01:00:02.046
Tell your Mom and Dad
that I'm starving.

01:00:04.670 --> 01:00:06.948
This is gonna be interesting.

01:00:10.296 --> 01:00:11.642
- Hey Bailey?
- Yeah?

01:00:11.677 --> 01:00:13.471
What do you think
of my new look?

01:00:13.506 --> 01:00:16.060
You two look like a couple of
badass GI Janes.

01:00:16.095 --> 01:00:18.753
Ooh Rah!

01:00:19.823 --> 01:00:21.687
Hey Morgan,

01:00:23.240 --> 01:00:25.656
I need to leave town for a bit.

01:00:25.691 --> 01:00:28.452
Haven't we been
down this road already?

01:00:28.486 --> 01:00:30.454
We stay off the roads.

01:00:30.488 --> 01:00:34.044
We have wings. Let's use them.

01:00:34.078 --> 01:00:35.528
Come with me.

01:00:36.253 --> 01:00:39.221
I'm not a dragonfly, Jordan.

01:00:39.256 --> 01:00:40.844
Look.

01:00:40.878 --> 01:00:43.260
I know it sucks that
your brain is sick.

01:00:43.294 --> 01:00:45.538
And fuck God or

01:00:45.572 --> 01:00:48.679
life or whatever, whoever it
is that did this to you.

01:00:48.714 --> 01:00:51.958
But it doesn't have to
be miserable.

01:00:51.993 --> 01:00:55.721
We can do anything we ever
wanted to right now.

01:00:55.755 --> 01:00:59.241
Like what? What can I do?

01:00:59.276 --> 01:01:04.419
You wanna travel, we can.
You wanna go skydiving, we can.

01:01:04.453 --> 01:01:06.732
Steal a car, rob a bank.
Swim with a turtle.

01:01:06.766 --> 01:01:10.839
I don't care what the plan is.
We don't have to wait.

01:01:10.874 --> 01:01:14.740
We have money and time,
let's spend them both together.

01:01:19.468 --> 01:01:23.334
I've always imagined
that one day

01:01:23.369 --> 01:01:27.407
I'd be wearing a
white vintage dress,

01:01:27.442 --> 01:01:29.444
my hair would be up,

01:01:29.478 --> 01:01:32.309
and my family
would all be crying,

01:01:32.343 --> 01:01:33.620
off to the side,

01:01:33.655 --> 01:01:35.277
with flowers everywhere.

01:01:37.486 --> 01:01:39.523
Now my hair is gone

01:01:39.557 --> 01:01:42.837
and my family will cry
for a different reason

01:01:44.079 --> 01:01:45.805
Morgan Gandara,

01:01:46.633 --> 01:01:49.188
my dragonfly boy,

01:01:51.328 --> 01:01:53.295
will you marry me?

01:01:55.677 --> 01:01:57.437
My brain could just
stop working.

01:01:57.472 --> 01:01:59.163
I can die tomorrow,
we all can.

01:01:59.198 --> 01:02:02.166
There's no line to wait in.
It just happens.

01:02:02.201 --> 01:02:04.790
You're serious, aren't you?

01:02:04.824 --> 01:02:08.690
Try to answer me by
asking another question.

01:02:10.002 --> 01:02:12.073
Yes?

01:02:19.080 --> 01:02:22.773
So, Jordan, that looks like it
was a pretty nasty fall.

01:02:22.808 --> 01:02:25.569
Thirty-seven steps,
hit every one.

01:02:25.603 --> 01:02:28.054
Must've really
pissed off the staircase.

01:02:29.815 --> 01:02:33.991
Dennis and I were saying how much we liked your new haircut.

01:02:34.026 --> 01:02:36.166
No, I never said
anything like that.

01:02:36.200 --> 01:02:40.791
Mom, I'm quitting piano.
It's getting too difficult.

01:02:40.826 --> 01:02:44.553
Okay.
I'll call Mrs. Randall today.

01:02:44.588 --> 01:02:46.107
Jordan, I didn't hear you
come in last night.

01:02:46.141 --> 01:02:47.971
Did you knock or just
creep up the back steps?

01:02:48.005 --> 01:02:49.973
- I let him in, Dad.
- What time was that?

01:02:50.007 --> 01:02:54.322
I thought you retired
from being a detective?

01:02:54.356 --> 01:02:56.738
We're getting married.

01:02:57.843 --> 01:02:59.016
Huh?

01:02:59.637 --> 01:03:02.054
Just like that, huh?

01:03:02.088 --> 01:03:04.332
Wow, this is awesome.

01:03:04.366 --> 01:03:05.851
We're in love.

01:03:07.853 --> 01:03:10.994
Under different circumstances,
the way I would approach this

01:03:11.028 --> 01:03:13.720
would be to ask
the both of you first

01:03:13.755 --> 01:03:17.138
but we're running against
the clock here.

01:03:17.172 --> 01:03:18.864
Moe...

01:03:19.623 --> 01:03:21.107
You hardly know this boy.

01:03:21.142 --> 01:03:23.558
How long did you know Mom
before you guys got married?

01:03:23.592 --> 01:03:25.111
That's a completely
different story.

01:03:25.146 --> 01:03:27.389
It is and it isn't.

01:03:27.424 --> 01:03:31.186
When'd you plan on having
this wedding? And where?

01:03:31.221 --> 01:03:32.498
Right here.

01:03:32.532 --> 01:03:34.051
Tomorrow?

01:03:34.569 --> 01:03:35.742
This is insane.

01:03:35.777 --> 01:03:37.917
I think it's a great idea.

01:03:40.471 --> 01:03:44.199
Morgan? This is what you want?

01:03:45.614 --> 01:03:48.169
This is all I have ever wanted.

01:03:54.796 --> 01:03:56.660
My sister is ordained.

01:03:56.694 --> 01:03:59.249
Yes! Aunt Lisa can marry us!

01:04:00.422 --> 01:04:01.665
Dennis?

01:04:21.305 --> 01:04:23.031
Congratulations.

01:04:31.453 --> 01:04:34.387
Score! I'm gonna
have two sisters!

01:04:34.422 --> 01:04:39.668
Uh, hey Dad...

01:04:39.703 --> 01:04:42.637
- Do you think I can borrow--
- Already?

01:04:42.671 --> 01:04:44.190
Seriously?

01:04:45.709 --> 01:04:51.508
Unless you have two vintage wedding dresses hanging in the closet.

01:04:51.542 --> 01:04:53.096
I have one.

01:04:56.927 --> 01:04:58.273
And I have the other.

